Date:  28/9/1871
Source:  Otago Daily Times
Author:
Vol / Page:  5
Edition:
Quote:  The honourable member for Wairarapa (Mr Bunny) had stated that the reason Wellington had not advanced as rapidly as the other Provinces was because there were too many educated men among its early settlers, and that these men either could not or would not work. Now he (Mr Buckland) had resided in Wellington for some months immediately after the arrival of its first settlers, and his impression was that there was a willingness and desire to work among all classes .
