Author:
Vol / Page:  19
Edition:
Quote:  Now that there is a town of 1000 or more inhabitants within a few miles of the Knapdale homestead, a railway within three or four miles, and good roads all round the estate, it is not easy to imagine the difficulties and dangers that its first settler had to undergo - no neighbour for miles; no practising doctor for 100 miles, no help or comfort in any way whatever.
